# CHANGELOG — bricklink-studio skill

Format: [vX.Y.Z] YYYY-MM-DD — Description
- Major (X): breaking restructure
- Minor (Y): new sub-skill or significant feature
- Patch (Z): fixes, renames, content updates

---

## [v1.7.0] 2026-04-10 — Parts Catalog: cross-system LEGO parts database with rarity scoring + model buildability analysis
- projects/parts-catalog/: NEW project — SQLite database from Rebrickable dumps + model analyzer
  - guide.md: full project guide with schema, workflow, rarity algorithm, model analysis, .io file structure, Quick Start for Team, DB repo reference
  - scripts/build_catalog.py: downloads 9 CSV dumps, builds DB; OR --download-prebuilt from github.com/uncurrent/lego-parts-catalog/releases; --check-update; --force
  - scripts/query_catalog.py: interactive queries (search, part details, color filter, rarest combos) + Excel export
  - scripts/enrich_bricklink.py: Rebrickable API enrichment (external IDs, images) + rarity score computation (0–100, 5 tiers)
  - scripts/analyze_model.py: buildability analysis (EASY/MODERATE/HARD) + --instructions mode for step-by-step layout extraction from model.ins XML (camera angles, page mapping)
  - recipes/full-catalog-build.md: verified 4-step pipeline recipe
  - recipes/model-buildability-analysis.md: verified model analysis recipe (Pochita + Toucan verified)
  - patterns.md: 7 confirmed patterns (+ .io ZIP structure with model.ins, + --download-prebuilt zero-config workflow)
  - failed.md: 2 anti-patterns (BrickLink API seller-only, Cowork sandbox blocks CDN)
- projects/_INDEX.md: added Parts Catalog entry
- bom-export/guide.md: added See Also link to parts catalog
- knowledge/INDEX.md + tools.md: added T05 entry for local parts catalog
- learning/observations.md: Rebrickable API as BrickLink fallback
- SKILL.md: added parts-catalog to Project Index

