## [v1.6.2] 2026-04-06 — Recipe system + Script-First Development principle
- Recipe system: `recipes/` directories in projects with formalized recipe format
- `projects/part-piles/recipes/_RECIPE_TEMPLATE.md`: template for creating new recipes
- Three initial recipes: recipe-1.md (Gaussian pile), recipe-2.md (crystal growth), coloring.md (palette application)
- `render/recipes/4-angle-preview.md`: render recipe using model_preview.sh
- SKILL.md: new "Core Principle: Script-First Development" section — behavioral rule for producing scripts as primary artifacts, binding to recipes, preferring recipes over improvisation
- Sub-skill guides: added "See also" blocks pointing to project scripts and recipes
- `projects/_INDEX.md`: updated with recipes/ and scripts/ directory conventions
- `projects/part-piles/guide.md`: added Recipes section linking to recipe files
- `learning/patterns.md`: new pattern — scripts should be saved and linked to recipes

## [v1.6.1] 2026-04-06 — Scripts collection: full Pockets pipeline bundled into skill
- projects/part-piles/scripts/recipe-1/: generator_pile.py, modifier_fill_gaps.py, modifier_settle_y.py, packager_io.sh, batch_generate.sh
- projects/part-piles/scripts/recipe-2/: generator_toplayer_v4.py, generator_toplayer_with_modifiers.py, modifier_rotation_shuffle.py, modifier_fill_small_parts.py, batch_generate.py
- projects/part-piles/scripts/coloring/: color_palettes.py, modifier_colorize.py, batch_colorize.py
- projects/part-piles/scripts/preview/: model_preview.sh
- projects/part-piles/scripts/archive/: 15 historical per-pocket generators (P6, P9–P14, P12 v1–v4, P12-BCD, mod_fill, mod_rotate, fill_gaps, settle_y) + README with algorithm evolution timeline
- projects/part-piles/guide.md: added Scripts Reference section with CLI usage for all production scripts and end-to-end pipeline commands
- build.sh: exclude updates/ from skill archive
- .gitignore: exclude updates/ from git (local contribution folder)

## [v1.6.0] 2026-04-06 — Full Pockets coverage: two recipes, coloring, production pipeline (P1–P19)
- projects/part-piles/guide.md: complete rewrite — P1–P19 overview table, Small + Medium size standards, full part list with dims, Recipe 1 (Gaussian rejection sampling: generator+fill_gaps+settle_y), Recipe 2 (sequential outward placement: touch-point formula, XZ-only collision, rotation_shuffle, fill_small_parts), coloring system (11 palettes, modifier_colorize.py, batch_colorize.py), production pipeline, batch generation, model naming fix (0 Name: {pocket_name}.ldr), render settings, macOS file association patch, Blender physics option
- projects/part-piles/patterns.md: 14 new patterns — Medium sweet spot (0% forced), Y-level separation, VIS_FACTOR=0.60–0.65, EXISTING_SCALE=0.65 on nominal dims, touch-point formula, XZ-only collision, gravity settle bottom-to-top, GAP decreasing through pipeline stages, N_ANGLES=96, TOP_K=10, pocket naming in header; plus P7–P10 patterns (tilt reduction for flat piles, 6–8% forced floor)
- projects/part-piles/failed.md: 11 new anti-patterns — Y_HERO_MAX too small, fill oval overflow, coverage=1.0 false positive, Small GAP=2 visual overlaps, Recipe 2 N_ANGLES=8 mechanical, always-closest concentric rings, GAP negative overlaps, 3D AABB for mixed-height piles, grid gap detection with AABB overestimation, Studio open -a failure, backtick key via AppleScript; plus P7–P10 anti-patterns (two-layer flat, Poisson disk XZ, 80 parts flat)
- learning/patterns.md: 3 new general patterns — Studio.app path on macOS, capture default perspective view first, three-step clean viewport for screenshots
- learning/failed.md: 3 new general anti-patterns — open -a for .io files, Quartz CGWindowID unreliable, (retained existing)

## [v1.5.1] 2026-04-05 — Fix duplicate SKILL.md in skill archive
